<div><h3>PHYS 310 - Condensed Matter Physics </h3>  <hr>Examines experimental properties and the quantum theory of solids. Topics include crystal and reciprocal lattice structures, the free-electron theory of metals, electronic band structure and the Fermi surface, lattice vibrations and the elementary excitations of solids.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=28&coid=93912" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93912&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93912&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt7918" target="_blank">PHYS 305</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> or permission of instructor.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered every spring<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt7918"></div></div>		</td>
